OL,6,FDavid Cledlyn was just 15 years-old
OL,7,Fwhen the war broke out. He's now 100
OL,8,Fyears-old but he remembers it well.
OL,10,F"We were in the Welsh chapel when the
OL,11,Fminister said the country had just
OL,12,Fdeclared war against Germany. And
OL,13,Fmother looked down at me in the pew
OL,14,Fand said, 'Forget it, you are not
OL,15,Fgoing to war.'"
OL,17,F"At 15 and two months, I joined my
OL,18,Ffirst ship. She saw me off on high
OL,19,Fstreet station and the last words she
OL,20,Fsaid to me in Welsh and English were,
OL,21,F'Promise me you'll be a good boy'.
