OL,6,F"I was just working at a machine,
OL,7,Ftyping from morse code to whatever,
OL,8,Fday in day out for three years. The
OL,9,Fmost boring job ever", she said.
OL,11,FIt might have been boring but it was
OL,12,Fan essential job which some historians
OL,13,Fclaim shortened the war by up to two
OL,14,Fyears. But Kath remains tight-lipped
OL,15,Fabout her experience.
OL,17,F"Were you a spy?", I asked her.
