OL,6,F"Oh yes. But don't tell anybody. I
OL,7,Fcan't tell you more, that's a secret.
OL,8,FIf I told you more, I wouldn't be a
OL,9,Fspy."
OL,11,FWorld War Two began over eight decades
OL,12,Fago, but the memories are still very
OL,13,Fmuch alive in Swansea.
OL,15,F"Words can't express what it means to
OL,16,Fme to be here today. It's such a
OL,17,Fmomentous occasion and I'm just
OL,18,Ffortunate to be alive to be here",
OL,19,Fsaid Royal Engineer, Ronald Horsey.
